snippet: Anders Behring Breivik, a far-right militant who massacred 77 people in 2011, was once a member of the Progress Party, which is expected to enter government for the first time.
abstract: Erna Solberg, Norway's incoming conservative prime minister, is preparing for coalition talks with Progress Party, anti-immigrant party poised to enter government for first time; fact that party may secure majority in Parliament has caused unease for some because Anders Behring Breivik, far-right militant who massacred 77 people in 2011, was once among party’s members.

byline.contributor: Mark Lewis contributed reporting from Stavanger, Norway.

lead_paragraph: Anders Behring Breivik, a far-right militant who massacred 77 people in 2011, was once a member of the Progress Party, which is expected to enter government for the first time.

headline.main: Norway’s New Premier to Meet Anti-Immigrant Party
headline.print_headline: Norway’s New Premier to Meet Anti-Immigrant Party
